1
00:01:08,300 --> 00:01:10,800
"Blue Lips"

2
00:01:11,200 --> 00:01:13,700
(Episode 1)

3
00:01:37,199 --> 00:01:38,199
Brother Mo.

4
00:01:38,500 --> 00:01:39,039
The usual?

5
00:01:39,159 --> 00:01:40,159
The usual.

6
00:01:48,800 --> 00:01:49,800
Thanks.

7
00:01:54,139 --> 00:01:55,139
Something on your mind?

8
00:01:56,260 --> 00:01:57,460
Nothing's on my mind.

9
00:01:58,320 --> 00:01:59,320
Just bored.

10
00:01:59,579 --> 00:02:00,739
Came to listen to some music.

11
00:02:03,920 --> 00:02:05,680
Are young people's
ears that bad these days?

12
00:02:07,099 --> 00:02:08,380
The new singer I hired...

13
00:02:08,880 --> 00:02:10,213
What do you think?
Handsome, right?

14
00:02:14,599 --> 00:02:16,319
Don't mind how loud his singing usually is.

15
00:02:16,559 --> 00:02:17,280
So many of these customers

16
00:02:17,281 --> 00:02:18,599
come here just for him.

17
00:02:22,239 --> 00:02:23,239
It's him.

18
00:03:27,460 --> 00:03:28,460
Xiao Teng.

19
00:03:28,960 --> 00:03:29,960
Late again today?

20
00:03:31,400 --> 00:03:32,400
Overslept.

21
00:03:33,280 --> 00:03:34,578
You can't run a business like this,

22
00:03:34,579 --> 00:03:36,039
slacking off all the time.

23
00:03:36,460 --> 00:03:37,840
You can't go on living like this.

24
00:03:38,340 --> 00:03:38,960
Just getting by.

25
00:03:39,320 --> 00:03:40,440
Taking it one day at a time.

26
00:03:41,219 --> 00:03:42,219
You...

27
00:04:00,099 --> 00:04:01,099
Defend! Defend!

28
00:04:11,800 --> 00:04:12,800
Don't rush, don't rush.

29
00:04:16,860 --> 00:04:17,860
Give me a second.

30
00:04:19,400 --> 00:04:20,500
Just a moment, almost done.

31
00:04:21,099 --> 00:04:22,099
Hold on a second.

32
00:04:30,480 --> 00:04:30,900
Almost there, almost there.

33
00:04:30,960 --> 00:04:31,360
Almost done.

34
00:04:31,579 --> 00:04:32,779
Just let me finish this round.

35
00:04:48,719 --> 00:04:49,719
What do you need?

36
00:04:50,239 --> 00:04:51,239
A box of Vandacon.

37
00:04:51,780 --> 00:04:53,019
Five-pack or ten-pack?

38
00:04:56,219 --> 00:04:57,219
Five-pack.

39
00:04:57,940 --> 00:04:58,940
Four hundred and fifty.

40
00:05:14,739 --> 00:05:15,739
Hey, kid.

41
00:05:16,579 --> 00:05:17,460
This is the fourth time

42
00:05:17,461 --> 00:05:19,420
you've bought Vandacon from me this month.

43
00:05:19,900 --> 00:05:21,180
If you're really having trouble,

44
00:05:21,380 --> 00:05:22,699
I suggest you go see a doctor.

45
00:05:23,480 --> 00:05:25,280
Taking this too often
has major side effects.

46
00:05:25,320 --> 00:05:26,320
It'll ruin your health.

47
00:05:28,480 --> 00:05:29,480
Stop lecturing me.

48
00:05:29,960 --> 00:05:30,980
You're young now.

49
00:05:31,280 --> 00:05:31,820
But when you get older,

50
00:05:31,821 --> 00:05:33,579
and reach my age, you'll regret it.

51
00:05:36,619 --> 00:05:37,619
Ending up like you

52
00:05:38,300 --> 00:05:39,660
is definitely something to regret.

53
00:05:44,260 --> 00:05:45,300
You've got a sharp tongue.

54
00:05:51,880 --> 00:05:52,880
What's his name?

55
00:05:53,000 --> 00:05:54,000
Wu Shixian.

56
00:05:54,659 --> 00:05:55,659
Wu Shixian.

57
00:05:56,380 --> 00:05:58,440
"Why should the sad zither have
fifty strings [sounds like Wu Shixian]"

58
00:05:59,119 --> 00:06:01,579
"Each string, each strain evokes but
vanished springs." [A Tang dynasty poem]

59
00:06:04,159 --> 00:06:05,159
Interesting.

60
00:06:05,320 --> 00:06:07,860
"Let me fall into the
bottomless abyss."

61
00:06:08,059 --> 00:06:09,440
Such depressing lyrics.

62
00:06:10,059 --> 00:06:10,699
Does he usually

63
00:06:10,940 --> 00:06:11,940
sing songs like this?

64
00:06:12,360 --> 00:06:14,539
Drinking and flirting to this kind of music

65
00:06:15,820 --> 00:06:17,180
doesn't seem quite right, does it?

66
00:06:18,440 --> 00:06:19,659
Well, they're young.

67
00:06:20,480 --> 00:06:21,480
Look around the bar.

68
00:06:21,820 --> 00:06:22,300
Besides you,

69
00:06:22,301 --> 00:06:23,901
who else is actually here for the music?

70
00:06:24,619 --> 00:06:26,400
They just want some background noise.

71
00:06:28,340 --> 00:06:29,340
Can I request a song?

72
00:06:30,039 --> 00:06:30,539
For him?

73
00:06:30,940 --> 00:06:31,940
Three hundred.

74
00:06:34,059 --> 00:06:35,059
I'll support your business.

75
00:06:41,679 --> 00:06:42,759
I'll request 'Pink Memories'.

76
00:06:42,760 --> 00:06:43,760
Sure.

77
00:06:53,360 --> 00:06:53,840
Wu Shixian.

78
00:06:54,039 --> 00:06:55,039
Someone requested a song.

79
00:07:02,940 --> 00:07:03,940
Who requested it?

80
00:07:04,800 --> 00:07:06,160
It was requested by that Mr. Teng.

81
00:07:11,239 --> 00:07:11,780
Hey, kid.

82
00:07:12,159 --> 00:07:13,019
This is the fourth time

83
00:07:13,020 --> 00:07:14,960
you've bought Vandacon from me this month.

84
00:07:15,260 --> 00:07:15,760
When you get older,

85
00:07:15,800 --> 00:07:17,599
and reach my age, you'll regret it.

86
00:07:18,980 --> 00:07:19,980
It's him.

87
00:07:25,900 --> 00:07:27,019
You want to hear a song?

88
00:07:27,980 --> 00:07:28,980
Just you wait.

89
00:07:30,960 --> 00:07:31,960
Here we go.

90
00:07:51,559 --> 00:07:52,799
This kid is pretty interesting.

91
00:07:53,260 --> 00:07:54,660
Turning a sweet song into a sad one

92
00:07:54,800 --> 00:07:55,800
is a real talent.

93
00:07:56,380 --> 00:07:57,620
Does he perform here every day?

94
00:07:57,960 --> 00:07:59,360
Tuesdays, Thursdays, and Saturdays.

95
00:07:59,400 --> 00:07:59,699
Why?

96
00:08:00,000 --> 00:08:01,520
Are you going to become a regular fan?

97
00:08:01,559 --> 00:08:02,639
With a character like him,

98
00:08:02,980 --> 00:08:04,760
I'd love to hear him sing every day.

99
00:08:28,880 --> 00:08:29,880
Quite interesting.

100
00:08:34,659 --> 00:08:35,119
Brother Mo.

101
00:08:35,319 --> 00:08:36,319
You're back.

102
00:09:15,640 --> 00:09:16,640
A'Heng,

103
00:09:16,739 --> 00:09:18,119
get me a whiskey.

104
00:09:20,619 --> 00:09:21,619
Waiter,

105
00:09:24,699 --> 00:09:25,779
I'd like to request a song.

106
00:09:28,159 --> 00:09:29,199
I want to request 'Love Sale'.

107
00:09:29,319 --> 00:09:30,319
Alright.

108
00:10:42,859 --> 00:10:43,859
Xiao Wu,

109
00:10:44,319 --> 00:10:46,140
do you have a grudge
against that older guy?

110
00:10:46,319 --> 00:10:47,479
He seems to be targeting you.

111
00:10:49,100 --> 00:10:50,100
Who knows?

112
00:10:50,739 --> 00:10:51,739
He's a psycho.

113
00:10:52,500 --> 00:10:53,079
But honestly,

114
00:10:53,359 --> 00:10:54,519
the guy might be a bit tacky,

115
00:10:54,939 --> 00:10:55,939
but he's pretty amusing.

116
00:11:00,100 --> 00:11:01,100
Xiao Wu,

117
00:11:01,460 --> 00:11:03,460
Sister Liu asked if you're free tonight.

118
00:11:03,779 --> 00:11:05,619
She wants to treat you
to a late-night snack.

119
00:11:10,239 --> 00:11:11,239
Just food?

120
00:11:11,579 --> 00:11:12,180
Or is there

121
00:11:12,460 --> 00:11:13,680
something else to it?

122
00:11:18,260 --> 00:11:19,260
If you ask me,

123
00:11:19,399 --> 00:11:20,639
Sister Liu isn't even that old.

124
00:11:20,960 --> 00:11:21,960
If I were with her,

125
00:11:22,079 --> 00:11:23,979
I'd save myself twenty years of hard work.

126
00:11:24,199 --> 00:11:25,199
Get out of here.

127
00:11:25,520 --> 00:11:26,720
Look at Xiao Wu's league.

128
00:11:26,960 --> 00:11:28,480
He's popular with both guys and girls.

129
00:11:34,300 --> 00:11:34,840
Well,

130
00:11:35,300 --> 00:11:36,880
then I'll go turn her down.

131
00:11:48,399 --> 00:11:49,399
Xiao Wu,

132
00:11:51,039 --> 00:11:52,079
it's a full house tonight.

133
00:11:52,180 --> 00:11:53,180
Give it your best.

134
00:11:53,600 --> 00:11:54,600
You got it.

135
00:11:56,399 --> 00:11:57,559
Sister Liu didn't come today?

136
00:12:00,439 --> 00:12:01,439
Hey,

137
00:12:01,479 --> 00:12:02,479
I'm just a singer.

138
00:12:05,199 --> 00:12:07,140
With people who just hang around bars,

139
00:12:07,680 --> 00:12:08,939
there's no need to get upset.

140
00:12:10,239 --> 00:12:11,479
Peace brings prosperity, right?

141
00:12:13,520 --> 00:12:14,640
I'm going to tune my guitar.

142
00:12:23,479 --> 00:12:24,060
Wu Shixian,

143
00:12:24,399 --> 00:12:25,759
someone requested a song for you.

144
00:12:44,180 --> 00:12:45,580
Are you messing with me on purpose?

145
00:12:46,260 --> 00:12:47,260
No, I'm not.

146
00:12:47,920 --> 00:12:48,680
How many times has it been?

147
00:12:48,840 --> 00:12:50,360
What kind of songs are you requesting?

148
00:12:50,779 --> 00:12:51,779
What do you want?

149
00:12:52,899 --> 00:12:54,300
I paid for the request.

150
00:12:54,960 --> 00:12:56,020
You're the singer.

151
00:12:56,600 --> 00:12:58,440
It's not like I'm asking
you to sing for free.

152
00:12:58,659 --> 00:12:59,020
You...

153
00:12:59,420 --> 00:13:00,980
Just tell me which song you don't know.

154
00:13:01,539 --> 00:13:03,699
I only requested popular songs.

155
00:13:05,020 --> 00:13:05,579
I don't know any of them.

156
00:13:05,939 --> 00:13:06,640
But those songs of yours...

157
00:13:06,779 --> 00:13:07,779
But what?

158
00:13:09,140 --> 00:13:10,479
I paid money.

159
00:13:10,939 --> 00:13:12,520
Of course I'll request songs I like.

160
00:13:12,840 --> 00:13:14,400
Should I request what you like instead?

161
00:13:14,979 --> 00:13:16,439
Am I right or am I right?

162
00:13:17,140 --> 00:13:18,140
Like hell you are.

163
00:13:20,079 --> 00:13:21,079
What?

164
00:13:21,359 --> 00:13:22,640
In front of everyone,

165
00:13:22,840 --> 00:13:24,095
you're going to assault a customer?

166
00:13:24,119 --> 00:13:25,779
And a paying customer at that?

167
00:13:26,479 --> 00:13:27,479
Do you want to get fired?

168
00:13:46,119 --> 00:13:46,579
Xiao Wu,

169
00:13:47,140 --> 00:13:48,140
are you okay?

170
00:13:51,460 --> 00:13:52,700
"Waiting for a millenium"

171
00:14:11,039 --> 00:14:12,159
What's wrong with him today?

172
00:14:14,079 --> 00:14:15,079
I don't know.

173
00:14:55,819 --> 00:14:57,339
If you don't know how to smoke, don't.

174
00:14:58,880 --> 00:15:00,159
You worry too much, old man.

175
00:15:03,979 --> 00:15:05,479
It's your body.

176
00:15:05,880 --> 00:15:07,500
Health is what matters most.

177
00:15:09,699 --> 00:15:10,699
Bullshit.

178
00:15:10,979 --> 00:15:12,220
I'm in perfect shape.

179
00:15:13,979 --> 00:15:15,539
In perfect shape, yet you buy Vandacon?

180
00:15:20,520 --> 00:15:22,076
If you don't want to host at Blue Moon,

181
00:15:22,100 --> 00:15:23,979
why don't you consider another job?

182
00:15:30,479 --> 00:15:31,939
Mind your own business.

183
00:15:34,020 --> 00:15:35,020
Fine.

184
00:15:58,680 --> 00:15:59,680
What are you doing?

185
00:16:31,100 --> 00:16:32,100
Off work, Xiao Wu?

186
00:16:32,979 --> 00:16:33,979
See ya.

187
00:16:53,899 --> 00:16:54,899
Hey, Mom.

188
00:16:55,399 --> 00:16:57,479
Did the fruit I sent you arrive?

189
00:16:59,159 --> 00:17:00,159
Yes, I got it.

190
00:17:00,359 --> 00:17:01,880
Eat it while it's fresh.

191
00:17:02,739 --> 00:17:03,739
Let me tell you,

192
00:17:04,140 --> 00:17:05,260
and don't think I'm nagging.

193
00:17:05,800 --> 00:17:06,979
Stop staying up so late.

194
00:17:07,300 --> 00:17:09,279
Don't always smoke, drink, and play games.

195
00:17:10,720 --> 00:17:11,800
The holidays are coming up.

196
00:17:12,000 --> 00:17:13,440
You're coming home this year, right?

197
00:17:15,220 --> 00:17:16,220
We'll see.

198
00:17:16,699 --> 00:17:17,180
Seriously,

199
00:17:17,181 --> 00:17:18,720
what exactly are you doing in Jinzhou?

200
00:17:19,760 --> 00:17:21,420
You haven't come home in years.

201
00:17:21,600 --> 00:17:23,359
You're almost thirty years old.

202
00:17:23,420 --> 00:17:24,539
You're not a kid anymore.

203
00:17:24,859 --> 00:17:27,500
Can't you just come back to Fengzhou

204
00:17:27,640 --> 00:17:28,920
and find a decent job?

205
00:17:29,300 --> 00:17:31,020
It would be so nice if you found a partner.

206
00:17:31,300 --> 00:17:32,579
Look at your classmates.

207
00:17:32,840 --> 00:17:34,280
Maybe they aren't wildly successful,

208
00:17:34,560 --> 00:17:36,859
but at least they've settled down.

209
00:17:36,960 --> 00:17:37,600
But look at you.

210
00:17:37,640 --> 00:17:38,699
Never at home,

211
00:17:38,819 --> 00:17:39,119
Hello?

212
00:17:39,341 --> 00:17:40,799
And you don't even have a girlfriend.

213
00:17:40,800 --> 00:17:41,800
Hello? Hello?

214
00:17:42,600 --> 00:17:43,119
Hello?

215
00:17:43,520 --> 00:17:43,939
Mom?

216
00:17:43,939 --> 00:17:44,939
Hello?

217
00:17:45,119 --> 00:17:46,438
Hello? My signal is bad.

218
00:17:46,439 --> 00:17:46,840
Hello?

219
00:17:47,380 --> 00:17:48,380
I'm hanging up.

220
00:17:50,100 --> 00:17:51,260
Honestly, this kid...

221
00:18:14,520 --> 00:18:15,520
Driving so fast!

222
00:18:17,579 --> 00:18:18,579
Are you crazy?

